gui.powermoney.config.cat.calculation=Calculation
gui.powermoney.config.cat.calculation.tooltip=Here you can tweak the calculations that converts energy into money.\\nYou can choose one of two formulas for calculating the energy price.\\n\\nLogarithmic formula:\\n    MoneyPerSecond = LogShift + LogBaseMultiplier * (log_LogBase(EnergyPerSecond) + 1)\\n\\nRoot formula:\\n    MoneyPerSecond = RootShift + RootBaseMultiplier * root_RootBase(EnergyPerSecond)
gui.powermoney.config.cat.calculation.logarithm=Logarithm
gui.powermoney.config.cat.calculation.logarithm.tooltip=Logarithmic money calculation.\\n\\nThe money is calcuated like this:\\n    MoneyPerSecond = LogShift + LogBaseMultiplier * (log_LogBase(EnergyPerSecond) + 1)
gui.powermoney.config.cat.calculation.logarithm.logbasemultiplier=Log Base Multiplier
gui.powermoney.config.cat.calculation.logarithm.logbasemultiplier.tooltip=The base multiplier in the log calculation.\\nEssentially how much 1 unit of energy per second is worth.
gui.powermoney.config.cat.calculation.logarithm.logbase=Log Base
gui.powermoney.config.cat.calculation.logarithm.logbase.tooltip=The logarithmic base in the calculation.\\nThe higher the value the less money the players get.
gui.powermoney.config.cat.calculation.logarithm.logshift=Log Shift
gui.powermoney.config.cat.calculation.logarithm.logshift.tooltip=The value that will be added each time to the final log calculation result.\\nHelps to adjust the energy price.
gui.powermoney.config.cat.calculation.root=Root
gui.powermoney.config.cat.calculation.root.tooltip=Root money calculation.\\n\\nThe money is calcuated like this:\\n    MoneyPerSecond = RootShift + RootBaseMultiplier * root_RootBase(EnergyPerSecond)
gui.powermoney.config.cat.calculation.root.rootbasemultiplier=Root Base Multiplier
gui.powermoney.config.cat.calculation.root.rootbasemultiplier.tooltip=The base multiplier in the root calculation.\\nEssentially how much 1 unit of energy per second is worth.
gui.powermoney.config.cat.calculation.root.rootbase=Root Base
gui.powermoney.config.cat.calculation.root.rootbase.tooltip=The root base in the calculation.\\nThe higher the value the less money the players get.
gui.powermoney.config.cat.calculation.root.rootshift=Root Shift
gui.powermoney.config.cat.calculation.root.rootshift.tooltip=The value that will be added each time to the final root calculation result.\\nHelps to adjust the energy price.
gui.powermoney.config.cat.calculation.calctype=Calculation Type
gui.powermoney.config.cat.calculation.calctype.tooltip=Choose the type of calculation.\\n - 0: logarithm\\n - 1: root

gui.powermoney.config.cat.payment=Payment
gui.powermoney.config.cat.payment.tooltip=Settings regarding the payment to the players.
gui.powermoney.config.cat.payment.currency=Currency
gui.powermoney.config.cat.payment.currency.tooltip=The currency to make the payments.\\nIf the currency specified here doesn't exist or is empty, then the system will fallback to the default currency.\\nOnly really needs to be set if there's more than one currency.
gui.powermoney.config.cat.payment.payoutinterval=Payout Interval
gui.powermoney.config.cat.payment.payoutinterval.tooltip=The interval in seconds between payouts.\\nThe value 1 means instant payouts (the money the player gets is calculated on a per second base).
gui.powermoney.config.cat.payment.moneyinterface=Money Interface
gui.powermoney.config.cat.payment.moneyinterface.tooltip=Which MoneyInterface to use.\\nCheck the debug log for available MoneyInterfaces. If the specified interface cannot be found or is "auto", the system automatically select one. It will prioritize mod interfaces over the Sponge API.\\nOnly really needs to be set if there's more than one MoneyInterface and default one is not the one you want to use.
gui.powermoney.config.cat.payment.simulate=Simulate
